message.content:
cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with measuring similarity between polygonal chains in Euclidean space, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the computational complexity of computing the distance measures and proposes an approximation algorithm. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper uses combinatorial arguments to prove the NP-hardness of the limited moves variant of the distance measures. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the computational complexity of computing the Fr\'echet distance and its variants. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses the concept of coordinated motion of two mobile agents to define the distance measures, which can be seen as a game between the agents.
